#Design Guidelines for Large/Emphasized Numbers (Stats & Quotes)
Hierarchy & Layout

Place the key number/value at the visual top or center of each stat/quote block.

Use a grid or flex layout for stat groups.

grid grid-cols-2 md:grid-cols-3 gap-6 is a solid default.

Typography

Numbers:

Use large font sizes (text-4xl to text-7xl depending on context/device).

Make numbers bold (font-bold or font-extrabold).

Use a brand-accent color (text-blue-600 or your brandâ€™s main color).

Labels/Supporting Text:

Place stat label/title above the number (text-lg sm:text-xl font-semibold text-gray-800).

Add a short description below, smaller and muted (text-sm text-gray-500).

Spacing & Sizing

Use vertical spacing between label, number, and description (mt-1, mt-2).

Apply generous padding to stat containers (p-4 to p-8).

Visual Emphasis

Use badges, icons, or % change tags for extra context, but keep secondary.

If comparing stats (like % change), use subtle background highlights (bg-gray-200/50) and rounded badges.

Accessibility

Ensure text contrast meets accessibility standards (check brand color against backgrounds).

Use semantic HTML (<h4>, <p>, <span>, etc.).

Dark Mode

Always include dark mode classes (e.g., dark:text-neutral-200, dark:bg-neutral-800).

Responsiveness

Numbers and containers should resize appropriately on smaller screens (use responsive font and grid classes).

Use sm:, md:, and lg: Tailwind prefixes as needed.

Consistency

All stats/quote sections should use the same spacing, color, and typography system.

Consider creating a <StatCard> or <QuoteCard> component to enforce this.

Example Pattern (React + Tailwind):

tsx
Copy
Edit
<div className="p-6 bg-white dark:bg-neutral-900 rounded-2xl shadow flex flex-col items-center text-center">
  <h4 className="text-lg sm:text-xl font-semibold text-gray-800 dark:text-neutral-200">Stat Label</h4>
  <p className="mt-2 text-5xl sm:text-6xl font-bold text-blue-600 dark:text-blue-400">98.7%</p>
  <p className="mt-1 text-sm text-gray-500 dark:text-neutral-400">Supporting detail here</p>
</div>
Quick Reference Checklist
 Large, bold, colored number

 Label/title above, description below

 Consistent padding and spacing

 Grid or flex layout for multiple stats

 Dark mode and accessible color contrast

 Responsive on all devices